crcl.utils

Class XFuture<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<T>
      • crcl.utils.XFuture<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object to be obtained from the future
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompletionStage<T>, Future<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    XFutureVoid

    public class XFuture<T>
extends CompletableFuture<T>
    An extension of java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture that allows additional tracing,cancellation and convenience compared to the base class.
    Author:
    Will Shackleford <william.shackleford@nist.gov>,<wshackle@gmail.com>
